Results and Discussion
Physical connections among plants through DSE
Our results provide preliminary evidence that a non-mycorrhizal fungus may connect plants in common networks, increasing the biomass of the networked plants and moving water between plants. Moreover, we found evidence in support of H1 with hyphae from donor plants crossing an air gap and colonizing the roots of receiver plants in the Permeable treatment from the main experiment but in none of the Impermeable or Axenic treatments (Figs. 2, 3; Supplementary Table 2). The DSE was also observed directly connecting the roots of plants grown in a clear substrate for demonstration purposes (Supplementary Fig. 2). These findings represent an initial step toward exploring the potential for network formation among non-mycorrhizal fungi and raise the possibility that CMNs are just one of several types of microbial networks connecting plants.
